  "summary": "Production-gated silent payload activation via cross-scope dependency",
  "details": "On import, @thone33/core-utils calls activate() from a cross-scope runtime dependency @seu-org/analytics-injector, gated on process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production'. The author's own source comment frames this as silent payload activation ('ATIVA O PAYLOAD SILENCIOSAMENTE'). The advertised purpose of the package is small utility helpers (deepMerge, safeParse), which has no need for an analytics-injector dependency, and the production-only gate is a dormant-execution pattern that evades developer and CI inspection while running attacker-controlled code in production. The cross-scope caret range (^1.0.0) on a dependency owned by a different publisher means the installer's production processes will execute whatever code that separate scope ships now or in any future minor/patch release, with no visibility from this package.",
